body:
Verilating:

```verilog
  always @(posedge clk) a <= b;
  always @(posedge clk) b <= a;
```

yields:

```
  __Vdly__a = vlSelf->a;
  __Vdly__a = vlSelf->b;
  vlSelf->b = vlSelf->a;
  vlSelf->a = __Vdly__a;
```

The first assignment is redundant. I wonder how many of these are there that the C++ compiler can't get rid of due to function splitting.
